PostgreSQL New Instance Request – Application Team Checklist (Tabular Format)
You can paste this directly into Confluence and convert it to tables, or copy each section as a separate table.

1. General Information
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Application Name	Enter the official application name.
Short Description of Application	1–2 sentences describing what the application does.
Business Owner (Name)	Person accountable for the application.
Business Owner Email	Email address.
Technical Owner / Primary Contact (Name)	Main technical contact for this application.
Technical Owner Email	Email address.
On-call Contact / Distribution List (if any)	Pager/On-call email list or group.
Environment(s) Required (Dev/Test/UAT/Prod/Other)	Check/select all that apply.
Purpose of Database Instance (transactional, reporting, analytics, etc.)	Brief description of how the DB will be used.
2. Data Classification & Security
Field / Question	Options / Instructions
Data Sensitivity Level	Public / Internal / Confidential / PII / Financial / Health / Other (specify).
Will the database store PII?	Yes / No – if Yes, describe type of PII.
Compliance Requirements	None / GDPR / PCI-DSS / HIPAA / SOX / Other (specify).
Is Encryption at Rest Required?	Yes / No – specify any standard (e.g., AES-256).
Is Encryption in Transit (SSL/TLS) Required?	Yes / No.
Will External Users (outside company network) Access the DB?	Yes / No – if Yes, specify how (VPN, private link, etc.).
Any Specific IP/Network Restrictions for Access?	List allowed IP ranges/subnets or security groups.
3. Connectivity & Network
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Application Name(s) Connecting to this DB	If multiple components connect, list them.
Type of Application	Backend service / Web app / Batch job / BI tool / Other (specify).
Source Networks/Subnets	List network segments (CIDR, VLAN, or subnet names).
Required Firewall Rules	Describe any special rules, if known.
DB Port	Standard (5432) or Custom (specify port).
Do Developers Need Direct DB Access (psql/pgAdmin)?	Yes / No – if Yes, list IP ranges or VPN info.
4. Capacity & Sizing
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Estimated Initial Database Size (GB)	e.g., 10 GB.
Estimated Monthly Data Growth (GB)	e.g., 2 GB/month.
Expected Data Retention Period	e.g., 6 months, 1 year, 3 years.
Approximate Number of Concurrent Application Users	Estimate or range.
Approximate Number of Concurrent DB Connections Required	Estimate or range.
Workload Type	OLTP / Reporting / Mixed – choose main one.
Specific Latency Requirements (if any)	e.g., “Most queries should complete < 200 ms.”
Peak Load Periods	e.g., “Weekdays 9:00–18:00 CET.”
5. High Availability & Disaster Recovery
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Target Availability Level	Standard / High / Very High (requires HA).
Is a High-Availability Setup Required?	Yes / No – describe expectations (automatic failover, read replicas, etc.).
Required Backup Frequency	Daily / Multiple times per day / Other (specify).
Backup Retention Period	How long backups must be kept (e.g., 30 days, 90 days).
Recovery Point Objective (RPO) – Acceptable Data Loss	e.g., 15 min, 1 hour.
Recovery Time Objective (RTO) – Acceptable Downtime	e.g., 1 hour, 4 hours.
Is a DR Setup in Another Region/Data Center Required?	Yes / No – if Yes, specify target region/DC and requirements.
6. Database Structure & Usage
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Do You Need a Dedicated Database for This Application?	Yes / No.
Do You Need Multiple Databases?	Yes / No – if Yes, how many and names (if known).
Do You Require Multiple Schemas?	Yes / No – list schema names if known.
Main Operations	CRUD / Complex joins / Heavy reporting / Batch imports/exports / Full-text search (check all).
Expected Largest Table Size (Rows/GB)	Rough estimate if known.
Planned Use of JSON/JSONB Columns?	Yes / No.
Planned Use of Table Partitioning?	Yes / No.
Planned Use of Stored Procedures/Functions or Triggers?	Yes / No – briefly describe.
Required PostgreSQL Extensions	e.g., uuid-ossp, pg_trgm, postgis – list if known.
7. Users, Roles & Access Control
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Do You Need a Dedicated DB User for the Application?	Yes / No – specify preferred username if any.
Required Permissions for Application User	Read/write / Read-only / Needs to create or alter tables?
Who Needs Direct Human Access (Developers, Analysts, etc.)	List roles and approximate count (e.g., 5 developers, 2 analysts).
Access Level for Developers	Read-only / Read-write / No direct access.
Access Level for Analysts	Read-only / Limited to reporting schema, etc.
Authentication Method Required	Username/password / SSO/IAM (if available) / Other (specify).
8. Non-Functional Requirements
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Preferred Maintenance Window (Day/Time, Timezone)	e.g., Sunday 01:00–03:00 CET.
Times When Changes/Downtime Are Not Allowed	e.g., Month-end closing, Black Friday, etc.
Application-Specific Monitoring Needs	Any special metrics or checks you expect.
Who Should Receive Database Alerts (Email/Chat Group)	List mailing lists or chat channels.
Required Logging Level	Default / Include slow query logs / Detailed audit logging.
Slow Query Threshold (if logging required)	e.g., log queries slower than 1 second.
9. Integration, Migrations & Dependencies
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Is There Existing Data to Migrate into This DB?	Yes / No.
Source of Existing Data	e.g., Oracle, MySQL, CSV files, older PostgreSQL instance.
Approximate Data Volume to Migrate (GB)	Estimate.
Migration Window / Time Constraints	e.g., must be completed over a weekend, specific dates.
Other System Integrations	Message queues, other databases, external APIs – brief description.
10. Version, Platform & Deployment Preferences
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Required Minimum PostgreSQL Version	e.g., 14 / 15, or “No preference, use standard.”
Hosting Preference	On-prem / Cloud-managed (RDS, Cloud SQL, Azure) / No preference.
Preferred Database Time Zone	e.g., UTC (recommended) or specific timezone if needed.
Specific Locale or Collation Requirements	Yes / No – if Yes, specify (e.g., en_US.UTF-8).
11. Timeline & Approvals
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Target Date When Database Should Be Ready	Date.
Planned Go-live Date of the Application	Date, if different.
Approved by Business Owner	Yes / No – name and date of approval.
Approved by Architecture/Review Board (if applicable)	Yes / No – name and date of approval.
12. Additional Notes
Field / Question	Example / Instructions
Additional Comments / Special Requirements	Any information not covered above (special SLAs, licensing, tooling, etc.).
